Title: 1972 Plymouth Scamp Valiant Dodge Dart Mopar Muscle Car 72 V8 Project
Description: Needs complete restoration. VIN plate in place and untampered with, but fender build code tag is missing. Comes with clean and clear North Carolina title in my name. This is a southern car that has never seen salt and has fantastic floorboards! It has minor and very fixable rust with some sloppy bondo work in the quarter panels and along lower rear roofline. The underside of the car, frame rails, doors, sills, trunk, hood, and decklid are all in good shape. Glass is all there and in good shape without excessive wear or clouding. It looks like it has been painted several times, but the original paint looks like it was Petty Blue. It looks like it was a highly optioned car when new, but without the fender tag I am not sure of exactly which options it came with.

I have no idea how many miles it has as it has no speedometer. It is an original console and bucket seat car, but no seats are included. 318 engine has been partially dismantled and heads are just sitting on the block. The tires hold air and car rolls easily, but has no brakes. It does not run obviously and will need to be towed. It is up to the buyer to arrange pickup or shipment. I will sell to anyone in the world, but again, the buyer must handle all arrangements. I can meet a shipper or the buyer themselves to assist with access to the lot, but loading is up to you. Car comes with a fresh and clear North Carolina title. This is a project that obviously does need a complete restoration, but it is an excellent start. You're not going to find another one in this good of shape for this kind of money anywhere.

The pictured parts lot can come with the car at the asking price, but if you don't need it we can negotiate on price. I also have a complete, built 318 4bbl engine with 20k miles on a stand, another known good 904 auto, and other various parts available separately if interested.

Title: 2013 Jaguar XF 3.0 Supercharged Only 42k mile- NICE
Description: If you want both Luxury and Performance then you have found your vehicle!
This car is in great condition and very clean inside and out.
The jaguar XF is impressive, stylish and full of power.
This XF is Equipped with a V6 3.0 Supercharged engine with an 8 speed Automatic transmission. The 3.0 Supercharged gives you 340hp and remarkable performance.

The XF is by far the smoothest ride I have ever driven. The electronic suspension provides you with a very pleasant ride whether your cruising or wanting to whip through the curves this thing will grip the ground and GO. If you are looking for speed, hit the checkered flag button and it will take the performance to a whole another level.
The appearance is stunning and definitely turns heads out on the road!

It is a Jaguar so you know it comes fully loaded, I will name some of my favorite features. It has all powered, top grain heated leather seats, touch screen navigation that has many options including Bluetooth for your music and hands-free driving, rear backup camera and parking sensors on the front and backside, also has auto adjusting mirrors which all make backing up easier. Blind spot sensors on mirrors. Auto bright headlights which means it senses oncoming cars and will turn your high beams off and back on accordingly. Auto start/stop which means the car has the ability to shut off at a stop light and automatically start back up when you hit the gas. Sunroof. Keyless entry and keyless start. Powered blind shade in rear window. Much more.
This car sold new for around 60 grand.

We are obviously offering you this vehicle at a significantly lower price. We specialize in Jaguar rebuilds and particularly the XF. I personally own a couple of these myself that we did rebuilds on, so I am a big fan. We purchased this vehicle from an insurance company after it was involved in a light wreck. We were SHOCKED that this car was issued a salvage title.

However, the vehicle has been completely repaired and has been issued a rebuilt title. We do have before pictures of the car if you would like to see them before purchasing. The front wheel was replaced along with the upper control arm and few other small pieces. There were NO air-bags deployed, this was a light hit and a very easy fix.

The state of Tennessee inspected the vehicle to assure the rebuilt has been done according to manufacturer specifications before issuing the rebuilt title. Having a rebuilt title does not mean anything in my opinion, the title looks exactly the same as a clear title, you can receive the same insurance on the vehicle as a clear title. The only difference is you are saving $$$$.

Title: 2001 Nissan Maxima
Description: I have a 2001 Nissan maxima. It has 267k miles. My mom bought the car some time back in the early 2000's, and was the 2nd owner. It has always been a midlands South Carolina car. My little brother drove it in college and following. It's been a great car. Still has all the power you'd expect from a Maxima, even even you're passing someone on the interstate.  Tires are great on the alloys! Sunroof and windows work. Cloth seats. It is dirty. It has dents and dings. People have brushed up against it from time to time. A deer ran into the side of it years back. It has clearcoat flakes. The armrest is broken. The alternator needs a replacement bolt, but it is held tight in place, and doesn't move. (People tend to lose the top bolt for some reason in these.) If I kept it forever, I'd probably do a tune up and change the engine seals. It does leak oil like an old Nissan. (We'll call it built-in corrosion protection for the engine bay, hahaha!) However, it'll crank every time, drive quickly anywhere you need to go, and do so reliably. It doesn't seem to be leaking any fluids other than oil. This is just an extra car for us, and I have loaned it out to friends who drive it thousands of miles without a problem. If you need a good starter car that you don't have to worry about denting, this is the one. The engines/transmissions usually go 400k miles or so, so it should be good for you for a while if you continue to take good care of it mechanically like my family did!

Title: 2002 Ford F-150 XL
Description: I have a well maintained 2002 Ford F-150 XL for sale. I have had the truck for 5 years and have had no major issues with it. My father and I replaced the transmission soon after I got the truck. Haven't had any problems since then. Has a 4.2L v6 engine and a 5 speed manual transmission. This was my daily driver until I suffered a knee injury and can no longer push the clutch in without knee pain. If not for that, I would be keeping the truck. I have an automatic vehicle that I drive now. The Ford has been sitting for about four days now but I crank it up every couple of days to keep it circulating. Three of the tires have about 6,000 miles left on them. The other is a newer tire at about half life. I have the other three to the set and will through them in the deal. They are also about half life. The truck does have a few dents and dings on it but is a very reliable truck. I have never been left stranded with this truck. Dents are from previous owner. Also has aftermarket Kenwood radio. Would make a good work truck or daily driver. Clean title. Asking $3000. Will trade for anything: bang, cash, atv. of equal value.

Title: 2000 Yamaha star 650 classic
Description: For sale, Yamaha Vstar 650 classic. This bike is my daily rider and it's in great shape with low mileage. All the fluids have been changed recently, along with new filters. Tires are in good shape with plenty of tread. All lights and turn signals work as they should. Paint and body and in great shape with no damage.

Bike comes new with windshield and saddle bags, there's a passenger backrest that I took of that can easy be re-installed. Brand new battery along with a battery tender and also a usb charger setup so you can charge your phone.
Bike is running great with no leaks or problems, just took it on a 1,200 mile trip and it ran great.

I'm a taller rider (6'3) so this bike ergonomically is a little small for someone my size but I made it work. I'm planning on selling this bike to move up to something more stretched out for longer rides.

This bike handles great on the stwisty roads around here so if your new motorcycling or just want a fun cruiser, I think this is a great bike. There is a ton of aftermarket support for this bike and is a staple for metric cruisers.
The title is in my name and ready to be transferred. Bike is inspected and needs nothing but a new rider.

Email me with you name, info and phone number and I'll give you a call to set up a time to check out the bike. Only looking to sell to serious buyers with cash in hand. No test riders with out cash and ID.

Entering the front door on the right is a brand new Bosch Tronic 3000T 110 volts hot water heater, beside it is a Pentair Shurflo water pump 115 volt AC,  brand new 3 tub Regency sink, one hand washing sink, new power breaker box, under the sink are one fresh  water tank 20 gallon, one waste water 30 gallon, mounted in top front of the trailer 18500 BTU Frigidaire air conditioner, going down the far side wall is one used United Commercial Heavy Duty Freezer in great condition,next is a Pro Stainless steel work top table with enclosed 2 underneath shelves,  next is a stainless steel storage rack with several shelves, next one  top of the line new 36" Radiant Avantco Gas Charbrolier setting on a 36'' equipment table, next is a new Avantco Gas Deep Floor Model Fryer, above the fryer and grill is a 6' NSF approved from Ventilation Direct Hood, on top of trailer connected to the hood is a brand new Up-blast Centrifugal Fan, coming back inside on the serving window side at back door is a used 5 month old 36" Double Door M3 Turbo Air Refrigerator Sandwich or salad  Prep operates great, next a used 5 months 2 hole gas Eagle Hot Bar waterless, next is a new Regency 5' X 18" stainless steel counter table with shelf and a key operated cash drawer, next is a used single door True cooler works great. Outside trailer is solid white, no decals or lettering, it has brand new 5 in all including the spare 8 ply tires and 5 15" chrome wheels, it also has connecting stabilizing bars for safer pulling you can use it or you don't have to use it, it has a screw up jack connected to the tongue, 2 5/16" ball hitch, on outside of back door is a LP gas holder and guard, trailer comes with 1 20lb gas tank already connected, all gas equipment inside has an emergency gas shut off individually,

fresh and waste water info. fresh water inlet front right side, fresh water overflow and air outlet right front, fresh water clean out located at right side front shut off valve, waste water dump left front shut off valve, 1 overhead ventilation vent with cover in center of top, this trailer has no leaks. Over all this is a great opportunity for anyone to start their own food business as it is practically new and will work as good as new. This trailer is 20' X 8'.5" gives you plenty of room to work and or add other money making equipment to suit your needs. This trailer is excellent built for any type food from hot dogs to BBQ and anything in between. All equipment is fastened down so traveling is a breeze and nothing moving around. Title: Handcrafted Solid Hardwood Beds Twin Full Queen King Bed Bedroom Set
Description: We are Mountain Mule Hardwoods, a small business in the Tri-Cities TN area making hardwood furniture and gifts. We sell mostly online and ship all over the country, but we would like to do more business locally. All of the furniture we make is custom made to order, and made from American hardwoods: ash, red oak, white oak, maple, ambrosia maple, curly maple, quarter-sawn white oak, cherry and walnut. Our furniture is finely sanded and finished simply in non-toxic linseed oil, to reveal the natural color and beauty of the wood grain. We build a lot of furniture for chemically sensitive people, often beds for people buying organic mattresses. With everything we build, we think about safety, usability, functionality and durability of our pieces for generations of use. We do not offer any wood stain, but some people buy our furniture unfinished to stain or paint themselves.

We do not have a storefront, but would love to hear from you if you are interested in getting a piece made. You are welcome to come to our shop by appointment, to select lumber, see our work in progress, or discuss specifications. We offer so many custom options, including different leg choices, mixed woods, beds set up for a mattress only or mattress + box springs, larger or smaller headboards and rails, etc. You can see more pictures and prices at our website www.mountainmulehardwoods.com and Etsy, or follow us on Facebook and Instagram. (Most Etsy prices include shipping, so please inquire if you want local pricing.) We deliver to Tri-Cities, Asheville, Knoxville, and even farther for larger orders. We do offer a discount when buying several pieces. Before you buy poorly-constructed Chinese-made furniture from a chain furniture store, consider getting something built to last from solid American hardwoods and supporting a hard-working family-owned local small business. :)

Title: Full Size Curly Ambrosia Maple Platform Bed Frame
Description: We are Mountain Mule Hardwoods, a small business in the Tri-Cities TN area making hardwood furniture and gifts. We sell mostly online and ship all over the country, but we would like to do more business locally. This bed is made and ready to be delivered. It was just completed (Feb 10, 2018) and has never been used. The price is significantly less than it would be to order one.

This classic bed design features a large headboard and footboard, both curved with an elegant simplicity. The wide rails and sturdy legs make it very strong. The bed pieces are finely sanded and the edges are rounded over to make them feel nice and smooth.

This beautiful and unusual wood can really make a statement in your bedroom! Ambrosia Maple is maple that has been infested by ambrosia beetles, which cause grayish blue to brown streaks over the golden or pinkish colored maple. Not to worry- once kiln dried, the bugs are gone! The head and footboard of this bed are also curly, which is not a common occurrence. Ambrosia maple is sometimes called wormy maple or ghost maple, because the shapes can look like ghosts. Because wood is a natural product, its beauty marks are normal, and may include knots, knot holes, worm holes, large streaks or sections of light or blond sapwood and/or variations in grain and color. These variations are what make this a one-of-a-kind piece.

Our bed frames are handcrafted from furniture-grade kiln-dried solid American hardwoods. Thoughtfully designed and constructed to last for generations, our beds are finished simply to reveal the natural beauty of the wood. With everything we build, we think about safety, ease of use, practicality and durability of our pieces for generations of use.
Headboard runs from 25.25" - 44.75" from the floor
Legs at headboard: 2.25" x 2.25" x 45.5" tapered, walnut
Legs at foot: 2.25" x 2.25" x 21.75", tapered, walnut
Foot rail: 14" curved curly ambrosia maple
Foot rail runs from 7" - 21" from the floor
Finish: 3 coats of satin polyurethane, more durable than our typical oil finish but NOT low-VOC

This bed is ideal for mattress and/or box springs with a total thickness of 10.5" - 12". If you have box springs, you will use 3 kiln-dried poplar support slats as pictured in the listing photos. If you have just a mattress, we will add a platform with 8 kiln-dried poplar slats.
Call, text or email us, and we will get back to you as soon as we can. If you are in our 423 area code, you might need to dial 1 + 423 before our number. We look forward to speaking with you!

Title: LIFTED DIESEL
Description: I have a 2006 lifted crew cab Powerstroke that I simply do not need. I love the truck as does everyone else who sees it. It looks great, runs great, and sounds great! I'm sure I'll forget something but here's my best attempt. On the outside: it has newer style towing mirrors with smoked lens', roof rack, LED light bar, black diamond plate low profile toolbox, Harley Davidson head lights with HID bulbs, nice jet black paint job with painted to match pocket fender flares, Moto Metal 20" Diesel wheels with great tread Mickey Thompson Baja ATZ tires, great sounding 5" exhaust, with K&N air filter. Behind the rear seat is a new single 10" sub with its own dedicated amp mounted under the rear seats, roof mounted flip down DVD player, and tinted windows. The "issues": there is a vacuum leak somewhere that makes the heat/air default to only blowing through the defroster and also causing you to have to manually lock the hubs for 4X4 and the vinyl cover for the center console is missing but is only aesthetics, I've just never bothered to recover it. Truck is super nice and a BEAST! I cant go anywhere without people wanting to talk about it and is super dependable, I would not hesitate to drive this truck anywhere at any time! Title: Happy Healthy Chickens at Margarets Roost
Description: Very healthy and active birds. Each of the breeds listed should lay an average of 5 eggs a week. Perfect for the backyard or the farm.

Our goal is to provide you with healthy quality poultry. Here at Margaret's Roost we raise high production egg layers in small flocks at a time to be sure they get the attention they need to grow as healthy as possible. Our chickens are raised on high-grade feeds and Rooster Booster vitamins, not just thrown the cheapest feed until they are old enough to sell. They are raised in tractors moved over fresh grass often throughout the week.
Full List of Open Sale Dates when chickens are five weeks old, feathered and ready for the coop. Call for current availability, some breeds might be sold out.
Our standard pricing when birds are 5-7 weeks old
Full Coop Combo/8 pullets and a rooster - $77
**When available Cuckoo Marans, Speckled Sussex and Wyandottes are $2 more per bird.
==🐔We do require a $20 deposit to get on the reserve list, we can take care of that with a card over the phone or with Paypal. Please Give us a call for further information.
We do not get any text msgs.
We are not people with "extra birds". The fowl raised at Margaret's Roost was bred and raised to live and thrive on your farm or in your yard.

Tired of buying "hens" and waiting on eggs, then one day you hear your "hen" crowing? Yep, now what will you do with "another" rooster? That's because in order to accurately determine the sex of a chick it must be done by an expert, not a breeder or farmer. Our experts look at hundreds upon hundreds of chicks daily. All of our chickens and are sexed at 90%-95% accurate from the day they are hatched.

Like our new FB page "Backyard Chickens at Margaret's Roost" We update it weekly so it is the est place to see what breeds are still available. Just google our name if you can't find us through the FB search.

We are by appointment only so please email or call to set up a time to come visit our farm. Leave a voice mail if you don't get an answer, we try to respond by the next day. Feel free to call and ask questions or even just to talk chicken!

Laying Hens- We have found the "magic age" for a chicken to find it's new home is between 5-7 weeks old. These are not babies. They are feathered out enough for a coop. We have done all the hard work for you. All you need is a clean/dry place for them to sleep, food, and water. Typically they start laying around 16-24 weeks old so you only need to wait about 11 weeks before you start looking for eggs.

Why don't we sale laying hens? At 5-7 weeks old these chickens are young enough to learn you as their care taker, learn their home before they start to lay, and it is the most efficient as far as price. We have found that it simply stresses the birds out too much to be moved from a place once they start to lay. We have seen them stop laying for 3 days up to several months. The age we sell our birds is perfect for them to learn their surroundings before they lay.

Title: SWR/Carvin tube pre 1000w power Bass amp
Description: SWR Grand prix tube preamp and Carvin DCM1000 in light weight 3 space rack.
The SWR Grand Prix is stunning in tone.  Clean warm tube preamp.  Better than the SWR heads.
Ultra clean until pushed and then the most beautiful subtle growl.  It can be driven to crunch if that's
your thing but this is not a distortion preamp, it is all about tube clean.  I've tried pretty much every
bass preamp made and this is the best tube clean preamp in my opinion.  These sell for $350 and up
when they rarely pop up for sale.  This is a vintage pre fender orig SWR california piece of gear.
Carvin DCM1000 - These are good sounding very dependable power amps that work fantastic for bass.
Unlike many power amps Carvins can go to 4 ohms in mono.  Most bass players want to run at 4 ohms
for punch and headroom and most power amps won't do that, carvins do.
3 space light weight rack bag.  Sorry it's peavey logo'd ;-)  It's actually kinda cheap but it's also light and small
Both units are in pristine condition.  Both units work perfectly.  They sound fantastic.
There is one mismatched knob on the Grand Prix.  Matching knobs are readily available.
The idea with this rig is to get great preamp tone and loads of power in an as small and light as possible
package without going to a digital power amp (the current small heads) which in my and many others
opinions just don't cut it.  This is real power and it sounds like it!
The Grand Prix is very versatile with very powerful EQ (check pics) it can cover a lot of tones.
It has the great subtle SWR defeatable limiter, the love it or hate it enhancer (I love it) and just gives you
a big round punchy tube clean tone that you can EQ how ever you like.  Very sweet in my opinion.
If you like clean tube tone with tons of power:  this is it!
I have 2 Kappa loaded 1x12 cubes I may consider letting go for the right deal but are not otherwise for sale.

Don't look like a scammer:  If you just ask if IT is available or similar I can not respond.  You must include something
in your contact that mentions the amp or something that shows you are a real person.  If i do not respond THAT is why,

Title: Vintage Pair of Epicure (EPI) M-150 Speakers
Description: Up for sale is a pair of vintage EPI M-150 speakers, these are rare and don't come up for sale often. There's no sound coming from the tweeters, but there is from the woofer. The cabinets are in good shape, especially considering their age. They're made in real walnut veneer, with solid walnut and brass accents and look like a fine piece of furniture. Check out the gold inlays! There are some bumps and bruises, but I've taken good quality pics so there are no surprises. They were produced between 1973-1976, and are 25 x 15 x 11, and weigh approximately 40lbs. Sold as is. Please contact me if you have any questions. Thanks for checking out my ad.
For replacement parts, check out a company called Human Speakers.
Here are some specs and info from the web:
RMS Power: 15 to 60 watts (very conservative rating)

The Model 150 offers all the musical benefits of the two smaller EPI models [ed. note: the Model 50 and Model 100] in an attractive, more easily positioned cabinet styling. Using the same great EPI 8" module, this cabinet attains a system resonance of 35 cycles. This allows linear woofer operation down to the primary octave of all musical material even when positioned in a free standing location away from the walls in the center of a room, or similarly in the center of a large bookshelf. Depending on the size of the room a two wall positioning may be preferable.

New construction and design principles are utilized in the Model 150 to provide an optimum combination of high performance and decorative cabinetry appearance. Functional in this design are the four anodized metal extrusions in each side which are first joined to solid walnut corner pieces are then attached mechanically to top and bottom caps (both one inch thick) where the walnut plugs are accented by circular brass inserts.

As a finished piece of furniture, the Model 150 is a handsome creation of gleaming brass, rich solid walnut and a dark warm grill cloth. In a vertical position its 25" height makes an attractive end table. An 11" depth and beautiful symmetry permit its use as a magnificent bookshelf system as well.

Title: Vintage Pioneer SX-1010 Receiver (Totally Restored)
Description: Up for sale is a vintage Pioneer SX-1010 receiver. It is in very good condition and was completely restored in 2013. (See pics for complete list of work performed). It is very heavy at 49 lbs, and was produced between 1974 and 1976. The SX-1010 was supposedly the unit that started the "receiver wars" as it was the first one to hit 100 watts per channel. The SX-1010 was Pioneer's top of the line stereo receiver, in 1974-1976. The condition in very good, I took high quality pics so there are no surprises. Please contact me if you have any questions. Thanks for checking out my ad.

A very nice Pioneer SX-1010 that was refurbished in 2013 - 165 Components replaced .  Output was measured with 1000HZ sine wave and 8 OHM load present - 144 watts per channel observed clipping . Test was performed for a 10 second reading period.
Included is a copy of the owners manual and the 7 page data sheet explaining everything

Features include an FM front end with dual-gate FETs, ceramic filters and ics in IF stages for sharp selectivity, quadrature detection, phase lock loop (PLL) stereo demodulator, all IC equipped AM section with linear dial, balanced positive and negative power supply with heavy duty components, and a phono equalizer with wide dynamic range and extremely close tolerances.
The twin tone controls permit precise shaping of sound and direct-coupled power amplifier supplies high output power with minimum distortion.
Power output: 100 watts per channel into 8Ω (stereo)
Semiconductors: 3 x FET, 5 x IC, 73 x transistors, 41 x diodes

Title: Custom Furniture - Perfect for Unique Spaces
Description: I love making things and spend a lot of my free time on personal projects. If you're looking for a custom sized bench, table, desk, shelf, chairs, bed frame, or something as small as a silverware drawer organizer.. I'd be happy to go over options with you. I studied fine art in college graduating with a BFA in sculpture and love the idea of mixed media pieces the most!

For me to get started I require photos of items you like. I have attached some things I have made this past year. Please describe what about the piece in the photos you like most. I will also need the dimensions of the final product and some color options you're interested in. Ideas can range from simple clean modern designs to wood burning an entire piece with images of bears, frogs, faces, or foods. I can build chicken coops, sheds, decks, retaining walls, ramps, hang siding, paint interior or exteriors, etc.. If you have a wood/material preference we can discuss this before committing to a design. Most of what I work with is salvaged or upCycled materials to help the earth and keep costs down to labor alone.

I have created items modeled after furniture designer sets like Pier One, West Elm, IKEA etc.. If you have had your eye on a particular furniture set let me know and we can work from there. All prices will be reasonable. The final cost will be determined directly by time and materials. I will be working for myself, for you, so it's all negotiable.
I look forward to working with you and collaborating. Email with questions, concerns, ideas, or if you need advise on a project your doing.

If you need help around your house I offer out call or handyman work for $15/hr. I can mow, trim trees, clean a pool, lay concrete, fix fence posts, replace siding, repair leaks, hang trim, frame and sheetrock walls, etc.. No project is unreasonable!!
Feel free to check out my artwork through instagram: https://www.instagram.com/dzicchiart/
As well as check out my website: www.spiritMatter.us

If you had reached out in the past and never heard back from me it's because I bought a house, built a workshop, renovated the house, landscaped the property, traveled long and hard for the holidays... And was living my best life. I'd be happy to go over options now that I am settled and ready to get back into working for others.

Title: Magnapack Magnetic bed cover
Description: Due to worthless spammers, I ask for "Calls only please".
This 520 series is in like new condition:
Magnet therapy involves applying a magnet to the skin or close to the skin to improve a condition such as pain.

The strength of magnets is described in terms of "gauss" or "Tesla." A Tesla is equivalent to 10,000 gauss. Magnets used for treatment usually have a higher magnetic strength than typical refrigerator-type magnets. Therapeutic magnets are most often in the range of 200-10,000 gauss. Typical household magnets are typically around 200 gauss.

People wear magnets to treat painful conditions including general pain, pain after surgery, low back pain, foot pain, heel pain, osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis, fibromyalgia, chronic fatigue syndrome (CFS), carpel tunnel syndrome, painful menstrual periods, nerve pain caused by diabetes (diabetic neuropathy), sports injuries, and migraine headache.

Magnets are also worn for treating water retention, wounds, male sexual performance problems (erectile dysfunction, ED), trouble sleeping (insomnia), ringing in the ears (tinnitus), cancer, multiple sclerosis (MS), Parkinson's disease, schizophrenia, obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD), post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), epilepsy, trouble controlling urination (incontinence), and many other conditions.
Magnet therapy is a big business. Worldwide sales of magnets for treatment is estimated at over $5 billion annually. In the US the market is about $500 million.

There is interest in magnet therapy for medical conditions due to the variety of electromagnetic fields that naturally occur within the body. For example, nervous system transmissions and related muscle contractions are associated with magnetic activity. The heart generates the largest magnetic field in the body. Several other activities in the body are associated with magnetic activity.
At one time it was thought that abnormal magnetic fields in the body might result in certain disease states and that magnets could play a role in making these magnetic fields normal again.

You may hear that magnets attract the iron in red blood cells, resulting in increased circulation. But this is wrong. The iron in blood cells is not in a magnetic form. However, magnets, in theory, could have an effect on other charged molecules in the blood and other parts of the body.
There isn't enough information to know exactly how magnets might work in the body to treat disease or pain.

Title: Fender Cyber-Twin Guitar Amplifier
Description: This amp is all you could ever want or need in a guitar amp.  Make almost any sound imaginable!  I have original price tag - $1699.99.  This amp has barely been used - I only play acoustic. Also comes with original canvas full cover. Preparing to move overseas - must sell.

Fender Musical Instruments Corporation is proud to introduce the most revolutionary and ambitious new product in its fifty-five year history: The Cyber-Twin amplifier. The first amplifier ever capable of Cybernetic Amp Design (C.A.D.) technology that actually re-creates circuitry, the Cyber-Twin utilizes both analog and digital components to instantly become over 120 of the world's most sought after classic and modern classic amplifiers tones. Fender's world class team of engineers have spent more than three years of research and development on this extraordinary new amplifier. From day one, the intention was to follow the long-standing Fender tradition of innovation, and to set the standard by which all amplifiers will follow in the future. The result is the future of amplifiers, the Cyber-Twin

Not another modeling� amp, the Cyber-Twin is a warehouse filled with the best of history's amplifiers housed in one cabinet, and whose electronic architecture literally reconfigures itself to become the amplifier that is selected. While a specific tonal quality may be digitally replicated by a modeling� amp to give a snapshot of an amplifier at a single setting, C.A.D. makes it possible for the Cyber-Twin to recreate the original amplifier's schematic and maintain its sonic personality, allowing it to become that amplifier.

Senior vice president of marketing for Fender, Ritchie Fliegler, explains, DSP modeling amps may provide a one-dimensional snapshot of a very specific moment in time where a certain guitar is played at a certain volume by adjusting its equalizer. Once you turn up the gain or lower the treble, that moment is gone forever, and so is the amplifier the DSP is trying to emulate.

C.A.D. literally reconfigures the Cyber-Twin's tone stack, as if there were a tiny robot inside with a soldering iron building each one of the amps,� adds Fliegler. Once the specific circuitry has been dialed up, the Cyber-Twin is an actual amplifier that delivers the living, breathing response of the original. If you dial up a classic Fender amplifier like a Bassman or a 65 Twin, you couldn't tell the difference if you were blindfolded.�

The versatility of the Cyber-Twin, however, does not stop at classic and modern classic Fender tones. While most Fender amplifiers feature a tone stack that's placed before the preamp, many other classic sounds are from amplifiers that have the tone stack after the preamp, like many of the popular British models. The Cyber-Twin has the capability of moving the tone stack either before or after the preamp, offering the best of American and British amplifier voicings.

With the familiar Fender control panel, the Cyber-Twin is playable right out of the box. There are 35 classic and modern classic pre-set amplifiers to choose from, which are accessible by a large control dial. Playing a Bassman, for example, is as simple as dialing it up and using the standard amplifier controls to get a desired tone. Using the world's most revered amplifier circuits its building blocks, the Cyber-Twin also allows players to design their own amplifier sounds. The Custom Shop function features 85 of Fender's own pre-set creations, all of which are fully adjustable to allow musicians to go as deep as they want into their own personal tonal preferences. Once adjusted, new sounds can be saved in the Player's Lounge for 85 added possibilities.
Four Quick Access keys provide instant assignment and recall of a player's favorite Amp Design pre-sets, all of which can also be accessed remotely with the included four-button footswitch.

The Cyber-Twin features 130 Watts of stereo output (65 Watts per channel) through 2x12� Celestion G12T-100 speakers (8 Ohms). Two 12AX7WA vacuum tubes are used in the preamp, and there are four tone stacks which can be placed before or after the distortion circuitry. The Cyber-Twin truly is the Holy Grail of all amplifiers, explains Fliegler. With Cybernetic Amp Design, we've taken musical possibilities to a level never before attainable with one single amp. What we've created is the future of amplifiers.

Title: Teeter Inversion Table for Back Pain/Therapy/Recovery
Description: Like new inversion table for back pain relief. This table helped me rehabilitate a herniated disk. Basically, you stand in the device, lock in your feet, and use the comfortable hand holds to invert your body from an adjustable level from horizontal all the way to completely hanging. This not only takes the pressure off your back, but uses gravity to create traction in your spine to draw fluid back into your injured disks. Works great! Also works great as a core workout machine for inverted crunches, twists, etc. The table is extremely well built and will likely last forever. Highly adjustable for people of all sizes and shapes. Easily folds and stores in seconds. Like new. Fix your back!
These tables sell for $300 - $400 online and at local stores. From the ads:

Title: 97 Fleetwood Southwind Storm 34 ft Class A RV Motorhome with Bunks
Description: We are selling our 1997 Fleetwood Southwind Storm.  It is 34 feet long and we have had it almost a year.  We've only been able to camp in it once, due to the upgrades we did lasting through camping season.  We absolutely love this RV and truly hate to think of selling it, but it would help us financially is the only reason we are willing to part with it.  When we purchased it last year it had a few minor leaks, which we sealed and repaired the damage inside none of the leaks we repaired we from the roof and the floor wasn't effected either.  We updated the interior during this process as well.  It has brand new laminate flooring, and new carpet around the doghouse.  New led reading lights in the bedroom.  We painted the cabinets with the high end enamel cabinet paint.  The shower and sink in the bathroom has been painted to update it with marine grade paint.  We also turned a wardrobe into a set of bunkbeds, so this RV would easily sleep 7.  The sofa is a jack knife sofa, and the dinette also converts to a bed.  The awning is functional, but has seen better days.  All the window awnings are in good shape minus some sun fading, except one which still provides shade but needs to be replaced.  It has a brand new CO2 detector, brand new queen size mattress thats only been slept on once!  It has an Onan generator.  The parking break needs to be repaired, we've always used scotches so it hasn't bothered us, but wanted to mention it.  As far as we know mechanically everything works well, and there aren't any leaks.  We aren't sure about the propane system and the furnace, because we haven't really tested them.  There is some staining above the shower that was there when we bought it, but it's not soft and hasn't leaked since we've owned it.  There are a few cosmetic flaws on the exterior, but nothing too bad.  We really do hate to even think about selling it, and are actually not going to be upset if we don't.  We've invested a lot of time, effort, and money into the upgrades and would be perfectly happy camping it for a long time to come.  It only has 38,545 miles on it and runs very strong.

Title: Antique Asian Hand Carved Furniture
Description: This is a hexagonal side stand/cabinet, hand carved wood with Asian art. 4 of the 6 sides have detailed carvings, & the other 2 sides have trim. There are 4 symbols on the very bottom of the 4 sides that are carved, (see pictures). The 2 doors on the front of the piece open up to reveal storage space, with an optional shelf. The top comes off it you so choose, and there are 3 6 sided glass pates for the inside or the top. Finally, as you look at the pics you will see that there are 8 wooden hand carved dragons, 2 of which go on the sides of the body that aren't carved, & the other six pop on & off the top piece. This piece is very complex, so feel free to contact me for any questions. I've tried to show all it's features in the pictures.
Please only contact me between 12 PM and 8 PM EST.

Title: Delta / Mini Kossel 3D Printer w/ Filament
Description: This is a "Micromake D1" clone. Perfectly running stock Micromake D1 firmware which is based on Repetier.
Prints PLA beautifully and has a heated bed so you can also print ABS and other filaments if you desire.

I have it dialed in to around 100 microns precision but I'm betting with a bit of tweaking it can become even more precise if you're that anal about it. Calibrating a Delta requires skills that are a bit too much for me to wrap my head around.

I also have a Tevo Tarantula Cartesian so I don't really need this delta. This delta works great and is much faster than a Cartesian printer. I bought it to learn from but I'll stick to my Tevo. It's easier for me to calibrate.
A backup of the original firmware is on the SD card, along with a customized version of Cura with a set up for "auto-leveling".

Comes with the partial roll of PLA you see in the picture. Looks to be about 1/4 of a roll which will let you make a lot of stuff. I can give you a quick down and dirty lesson showing how to use the Cura auto-leveling feature but that is the extent of the "technical support" I will be able to offer.
There is tons of support available online including a Micromake Facebook group that I gained plenty of help and knowledge from.

Title: Travel Trailer, Former Food Truck: 17 Feet of Groovy
Description: This 1969 camper has been refurbished and was used in food service in SC. The motif is silver, black, white and red. There are pinstripes along the sides with delicate red flames that were applied to shiny, solid metal siding. No leaks! The rims are custom red ones with newer Goodyear tires of thick tread. The box is 17 feet, tongue hitch adds 2-3 more ft. I do not know the towing weight.

The floor was redone with black and white vinyl tile to match the black cushion upholstery. The cabinets were all refaced with a textured black metal that gives it a mod look. There is a newer refrigerator/freezer unit, in addition to a vintage electric/propane combo fridge above it. There is a 4 burner stove top with an oven. Wall outlets work and there is lighting. The ice-cold air conditioner is a quality Dometic combo air/heat ceiling unit that matches the black cabinets. There is adequate working space with facilities for a food service operation.

The kitchen table converts to a full-sized bed. The bench seat area also allows for a full-sized mattress. Storage is abundant and throughout camper seats and overhead. A small drop-down table top is opposite the back wall, which was converted into a hatch that opens wide and can be secured open by chains to attach to embedded hooks. (See silver hatch in photo to view size). I understand it was open to an outdoor grill and allowed the passing of food items back and forth for rapid production. Plenty of windows light it up with sunshine. An exterior aluminum window cover folds down over the front windows. This camper makes a suitable dwelling for 1-2 people, especially a couple. No bathroom, but spacious open area in back allows room for commode and portable shower set-up for the savvy soul. Kitchen sink drains out through outflow pipe under exterior of camper.

There is an awning and pull-out metal stairs. One portion of a panel of jalousie window cracked and has been sealed in with gorilla tape, no leaks. Included is a pre-cut pane of glass to fit the panel. There is also one other crack across one other window panel, though sealed and leak-proof. The tiles have seen traffic, though they are still intact, small areas of wear are evident. One small area of wood paneling has become frayed on the surface, yet the thickness of the wall is fully intact. There is a key for the door to lock up.

We love this camper, but are upgrading in other areas of life, so we will sell her to a good home. Because SC does not require a title for trailers, it does not have one. A NC title can be applied for using the "home made" trailer designation, similarly to a new tiny home title, if you plan to roll her far and wide. A long RV 120 volt power cord for 30-amp service is included. Love and blessings will carry along with her into a life.

For you tech-heads...here is Mackie's Technical Specifications on this Mixing Board.

The CFX™ Series mixers are comprised of stereo graphic equalizer and digital effects built in. The EMAC™ 32-bit digital effects processor was custom designed by our digital engineers and rivals the sound of many high-quality outboard processors. Like all of Mackie Designs' mixers, the CFX Series mixers are designed for rugged, day-in and day-out road use. Their sturdy-yet-light steel monocoque construction houses rugged, double-sided SMT-plated fiberglass circuit boards, and 60 mm faders with ultra-tight lip seals for keeping out dust and other contaminants. Impact resistant knobs are mounted so they "ride" just above the steel chassis--they absorb impact without trouble. Furthermore, they're designed to last, thanks to co-molded potentiometers that do not get brittle and crack up. Metal stand-offs are used at regular intervals to mount thick fiberglass circuit boards inside the mixer. These are extremely flexible mixers, not only because of their multiple input/output configurations, but also because of their 4 subgroups, 9-band graphic EQ, and built-in digital effects.

The CFX•20 has 16 mic/line channels and two stereo line input channels. All mic/line channels have unbalanced inserts. Each channel strip has one external and one internal/external effects send plus two aux sends, pan, mute, solo (PFL), bus assigns, and 60 mm log-taper fader. The mic/line channels also have input trim controls with individual Zero Level LEDs, 3-band EQ with swept midrange, and 100 Hz low cut filters. Two separate stage monitor mixes can be created with their own effects levels.

The CFX Series is a true 4-bus mixer, with four sub bus faders and master ganged Left/Right fader. Outputs include XLR and TRS balanced/unbalanced main outputs, a 75 Hz low-pass subwoofer XLR output, extra TRS

This offer is for a "Dual Autographed" Jim Riley's Signature 8" X 14" Ludwig Black Magic Stainless Steel Snare Drum. This Snare Drum was designed by Jim Riley and manufactured and sold by Ludwig, who endorses Jim Riley, the Drummer and Band Leader of Rascal Flatts. This is a very rare drum and the only one available on craigslist, Ebay or like it in the world. In fact, it's the only autographed one I've ever seen listed anywhere. It's certainly one any collector must have for their private collection. It is in like new condition with three small wear spots on the rims...see attached pics of highlighted area. The owner of the Drum Center in Reno, Nevada that I purchased it from stated these spots may have been caused by a microphone mount during the Drum Clinic he sponsored for Jim Riley in 2013. If you wasn't looking for them you would probably never see them. They are that small, faint and unnoticeable.

This Snare Drum comes with a new, unplayed and autographed 14" Remo Weatherking Tattoo Skyn Head that was signed by Jim Riley and also comes with the original REMO Weatherking Ambassador Snare side head. The original unsigned 14" REMO Weatherking Coated Ambassador Batter Head, that Jim actually played on this Snare Drum during this clinic, is also included with this auction.

As you can see...Jim Riley, the drummer and band leader of Rascal Flatts, signed the interior and top head of his signature snare drum manufactured by Ludwig. It was signed on March 5, 2014 before my first private drum lesson with Jim at his Drum Dojo in Goodlettsville, TN. The Drum Dojo is in the basement of his home and this drum was signed on both the inside and on the 14 inch Tattoo Skyn Head. According to the owner of the Reno, Nevada Drum Center / Music Store I purchased it from, Jim Riley is the only person to ever play this snare drum during a clinic that he sponsored in 2013. I purchased it from this Music Store / Drum Center and had Jim sign it during my first private drum lesson on the date noted above. A pic of Jim Riley and myself will be provided electronically as proof of the above statement. Very few of these Jim Riley Black Magic Stainless Snare Drums were ever produced and far fewer were signed by Jim Riley. I'll guarantee mine is the only one with Jim's autograph on a Tattoo Skyn Drum Head anywhere in the world! I know...I checked!!!

Title: LCR Set of NHT Model 1.1 Bookshelf Speakers, Mirror Gloss Finish!
Description: This listing is for one set of Now Hear This (NHT) Model 1.1 home theater speakers. Included are a pair of Model 1.1 and one Model 1.1c. These speakers have all been refoamed with great care and perform perfectly. They are in fantastic cosmetic condition, holding their classy black lacquer finish perfectly.

The Model 1.1 bookshelf speakers have a unique angled front baffle which angle the drivers to face towards the main listening position. This allows the speakers be be placed in an aesthetically pleasing manner while maintaining optimal sound fidelity. The Model 1.1c excludes this angled baffle so that it can also be placed directly in front of the listening position. The 1.1c lacks the NHT logo branding on the grill so that you can place it horizontally and still have it appear aesthetically pleasing.

The Model 1.1 and 1.1c were intelligently designed to have uniform sound production across your front soundstage. It is very common to find modern center channel speakers which have multiple woofers which are different sizes than the woofers in the left and right speakers. This produces issues with phasing as well as issues with overall coherence. NHT built the 1.1c to be identical to the 1.1 in order to eliminate these issues. The cabinet of the 1.1c is obviously a different shape than the 1.1, but its dimensions have been adjusted to keep the same internal volume. These speakers were very well thought out. It is always ideal to perfectly match your front LCR speakers.

I'm selling the same set on eBay for $275 with 15 Watchers. I'm offering a good discount to local buyers. I prefer to be contacted via text at (828) SE\/EN Six 8 - 2 2 Nine 2. Title: 87 Toyota 22-RE - Tiny Home, Work Truck, Flatbed dually
Description: I have a very unique Toyota truck/camper for sale. I acquired this camper when a client was short on payment for Carpentry work completed about 2 years ago. I gutted the interior part of the camper due to it being filthy, and in disrepair. I had high hopes at the time to rebuild into a Tiny Home. After sitting in our yard for 6 months my girlfriend said enough is enough mainly because of the wonderful custom paint job (you'll see in pictures) and I relocated to a storage facility where it sat and I had no ambitions to work on it anymore...main reason...no electricity.  I would periodically go and crank it up and just check on it in general.

This thing is sweet hence why I took it for payment on work completed the odometer reads right at 69,000 miles roughly. The backstory I have on it is a guy parents lived in this thing full time only changing campsites 3 times in 15 years and when they passed away he was left with it. It makes perfect sense due to the very low miles. Apparently the engine is highly sought after, early on after ownership I was offered $1,200 for the engine at one time and I declined due to following my vision of a tiny home.

I gutted the interior camper shell due to it being pretty nasty and mostly in disrepair. My plans were to rebuild into a tiny home to periodically travel and stay in. I dropped all plumbing and replaced some rotten flooring. I did leave the generator intact as you'll see in pictures.

This thing has never failed to start it literally amazes me every single time I would go and crank it she'd fire right up. I have never did an oil change or anything mechanically other than a new battery. The storage facility where it was being kept has closed due to a death in the family, so here I am..ready to sell it and let someone give this thing some love and put it to great use. It is very clean considering its age.
One could rebuild the interior for a tiny home/work truck/ or pull the camper off and make a 16' flatbed dually. The possibilities are endless.
Come take a look and see for yourself.
